setCctpDomain.t.sol
├── when caller does not have the relevant role
│  └── it should revert with AccessManagedUnauthorized
└── when caller has the relevant role
   ├── when the provided EVM chain ID is equal to zero
   │  └── it should revert with ZeroChainId
   └── when the provided EVM chain ID is non-zero
      ├── when the provided EVM chain ID is equal to Mainnet chain ID (1)
      │  └── it should revert with ProtectedChainId
      └── when the provided EVM chain ID is not equal to Mainnet chain ID (1)
         ├── when the provided CCTP domain is equal to Mainnet domain (0)
         │  └── it should revert with ProtectedCctpDomain
         └── when the provided CCTP domain is not equal to Mainnet domain (0)
            ├── it should associate the provided IDs in contract storage
            ├── it should clean up any previous associations involving either ID
            └── it should emit a CctpDomainRegistered event
